The Akwa Ibom State Ministry Of Health has appointed Dr Ntiense Rapheal Umoette as the State Epidemiologist with immediate effect. A press statement signed by the state commissioner for Health Dr Dominic Ukpong and made available to LEADERSHIP Sunday indicated that Umoette’s appointment is an internal reorganisation to match skills and competence to role. Until her appointment, Dr. Umoette was Deputy State Epidemiologist. She is a graduate of Medicine and Surgery and holds a Master of Public Health, Medical Epidemiology Practice. She has also attended several World Health Organisation training programmes. Her awards and accolades include: -Presidential Award for Meritorious Service for Ebola Response – Monrovia, Liberia – 2015. Africa Union (AU) Award of Excellence for ASEOWA participation – Addis Abba, Ethiopia -2015. Full MPH Scholarship Award to NFELTP -2014. Dr. Umoette is a member of several professional bodies including Nigeria Medical Association, Akwa Ibom State Chapter,  and the Nigeria Field Epidemiology and Laboratory Training Program (NFELTP). She brings to bear a wealth of experience and expertise acquired in the course of her career and from the several training programmes she has attended. The state  new epidemiologist succeeded  Dr Aniekeme Uwa who has been reassigned.